“Practicing dentistry” means an activity in which a person:
(A) undertakes by any means or method to diagnose or profess to diagnose or to treat or profess to treat or to prescribe for or profess to prescribe for any lesions, diseases, disorders, for deficiencies of the human oral cavity, teeth, gingiva, maxilla, or mandible or adjacent associated structures;
(B) extracts human teeth or corrects malpositions of the teeth or jaws;
(C) furnishes, supplies, constructs, reproduces, or repairs prosthetic dentures, bridges, appliances, or other structures to be used or worn as substitutes for natural teeth or adjusts those structures, except on the written prescription of a duly licensed dentist and by the use of impressions or casts made by a duly licensed and practicing dentist;
(D) administers general dental anesthetics;
(E) administers local dental anesthetics, except dental hygienists as authorized by Board rule; or
(F) engages in any of the practices included in the curricula of recognized dental colleges.

